---
import SkillIcon from './SkillIcon.astro';
import { focus, familiar } from '../utils';
---

<section
  class='clear-both sm:mt-[20rem] sitw pt-32 2k:pt-40 4k:pt-60 text-white font-poppins 4k:max-w-[95rem] 2k:max-w-[63rem] max-w-[40rem] md:max-w-[50rem] w-11/12 mx-auto text-center mb-32'
>
  <h2 class='font-semibold text-2xl 2k:text-3xl 4k:text-5xl'>Who am I ?</h2>
  <p
    class='tracking-wide leading-7 mt-7 4k:mt-12 2k:text-xl 4k:text-3xl 2k:leading-9 4k:leading-[3.2rem] mx-auto'
  >
  I'm a software engineer with a bit more than a year's experience, primarily focused on front-end development. 
  My passion is building applications that truly serve users' needs and address real-life challenges. 
  Currently, I'm humbly diving into server-side technologies like Node.js,PHP and exploring the intricacies of databases to broaden my skill set.
  </p>
  <h3 class='text-xl mt-16 2k:text-2xl 4k:text-4xl 4k:mt-24'>I mainly focus on</h3>
  <div class='flex flex-wrap justify-center mt-6 gap-8 2k:gap-12 4k:mt-12 mx-auto 4k:gap-16'>
    {focus.map((props) => <SkillIcon {...props} />)}
  </div>
  <h3 class='text-xl mt-16 2k:mt-22 2k:text-2xl 4k:text-4xl 4k:mt-24'>
    I am familiar working with
  </h3>
  <div class='flex justify-center flex-wrap mt-6 gap-8 4k:mt-16 mx-auto 2k:gap-12 4k:gap-16'>
    {familiar.map((props) => <SkillIcon {...props} />)}
  </div>
</section>
